WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
The Knox Guard Overdue payment wallpaper policy is an advanced 

2
00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.891
feature that allows you to display a warning wallpaper on a device's home and lock screens, 

3
00:00:08.891 --> 00:00:12.532
encouraging users to fulfill any outstanding payments. 

4
00:00:13.233 --> 00:00:17.233
To use this feature, you must have a Knox Guard Advanced license. 

5
00:00:17.233 --> 00:00:19.857
Get started by going to the Policies page, 

6
00:00:19.858 --> 00:00:23.866
then under Advanced controls click Overdue payment wallpaper.

7
00:00:24.566 --> 00:00:26.829
Select an image to upload.

8
00:00:26.830 --> 00:00:31.466
Note that the image must be less than 5 megabytes, and in PNG format.

9
00:00:31.700 --> 00:00:34.666
Once uploaded, preview the image and click Save.

10
00:00:34.666 --> 00:00:37.866
After creating this policy, you can apply it to your devices. 

11
00:00:37.866 --> 00:00:42.132
To do this, go to the Devices page and select one or more devices.

12
00:00:42.133 --> 00:00:47.366
Under Actions, click Manage Policy, then select Apply overdue payment wallpaper.

13
00:00:47.700 --> 00:00:51.333
Preview your wallpaper configuration, and click Apply. 

14
00:00:51.333 --> 00:00:55.979
Once applied, users will persistently see the wallpaper on their devices 

15
00:00:55.979 --> 00:00:59.032
and will be unable to change it until you remove the policy.

16
00:01:00.266 --> 00:01:04.699
To remove the policy, select one or more devices, then click Actions, 

17
00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:09.600
followed by Manage Policy, and then select Remove overdue payment wallpaper.

18
00:01:09.866 --> 00:01:15.066
Once the policy is removed, device users can revert the wallpaper back to its previous image.

19
00:01:15.633 --> 00:01:21.136
Alternatively, you can apply the Overdue payment wallpaper policy from the Bulk Actions page.

20
00:01:21.137 --> 00:01:25.466
To do this, click Bulk actions in the left navigation pane. 

21
00:01:25.466 --> 00:01:30.118
Under Advanced controls, click Manage overdue payment wallpaper restriction. 

22
00:01:30.119 --> 00:01:34.466
Then on the following page, select Apply overdue wallpaper restriction.

23
00:01:34.466 --> 00:01:40.466
Next, upload a CSV or XLS file containing your device IDs and click Apply. 

24
00:01:41.366 --> 00:01:44.519
If you want to remove this policy from multiple devices at once, 

25
00:01:44.520 --> 00:01:46.931
you can use the same bulk action process, 

26
00:01:46.931 --> 00:01:50.199
but select Remove overdue wallpaper restriction instead. 

27
00:01:52.200 --> 00:01:54.513
For additional Knox Guard help at any time, 

28
00:01:54.513 --> 00:01:58.199
see our documentation at docs.samsungknox.com. 

29
00:01:58.200 --> 00:01:59.200
Thanks for watching!

